oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Proceedings of the Twenty-Eighth Annual Conference (1995). Opening Ceremony, Student Reception, and Events
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Bovine Practitioners, American Association of
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The Opening Ceremony of the 28th Annual AABP Convention was held at the Convention Center, San Antonio, Texas on Thursday evening, September 14. It was preceded by the traditional hospitality hour where newcomers were greeted and old friendships were renewed over sumptuous hors d'oeuvres and refreshments. The AABP sponsored a reception for over 100 students who attended the meeting, immediately after the OpeningCeremony, at the Hilton Palacio del Rio. Also detailed are various local tours and an Evening with Baxter Black, cowboy humorist.
